title: For Sale:  Model 1893/95 "Boer Model" Chilean Mauser
postcontent: This is an 1893/1895 Transvaal-contract Chilean Mauser in 7mm Mauser. This rifle was built under contract by DWM for the South African Republic (Transvaal) during the Boer War. Due to the British blockade of Portuguese West Africa at the time, this rifle was sent back to DWM and resold to Chile (this is indicated by its "C" prefix). This rifle is in excellent condition especially considering it is almost 120 years old and has been to four continents. It features a Chilean crest on the receiver, there is minimal wear on the stock and receiver, and the bore is still shiny. Overall, these rifles are great shooters known for their light recoil and flat trajectory. A testament to this fact are stories of Boer marksmen being able to hit British soldiers almost 1000 yards away in the open Veld of South Africa. This is a great chance to own a piece of history, and would make an excellent addition to any collection of mausers or antique military firearms. Please feel free to contact Aaron for more information and pictures: 814 516 62-seven-nine

title: For Sale:  New Custom Diana 56TH .22 Spring Piston Rifle 22 Built by Héctor J. Medina G. of CT Custom Airguns
postcontent: Well folks, I am selling a custom tuned new Diana 56TH in .22 caliber. This is one of Diana's recoilless rifles and is very accurate out of the box and even more so now. I commissioned this rifle to be built by Héctor J. Medina G.- Airgunsmith of CT Custom Airguns LLC. For you folks who don't know about Héctor, he is a wizard at tuning Diana air rifles and a great guy to deal with. This rifle was completed and delivered to me in May 2017 This .22 caliber 56TH has been completely tuned and here is a list of some of what he did: - Tuned the ZR scope mount - Installed and zeroed a new Vortex 6-24x50 Crossfire II scope - Best pellet identified as JSB Jumbo Express 14.3 grain pellets (see photo of various pellet groups @ 35 yards) - Installed a HMO piston and HMR breach seal to support heavier pellets - Titan XS spring with a moly infused nylon guide yielding 22 ft lbs of energy - Put the rifle in a Plano hard case for safe transport Hector put 1,200 pellets while tuning the rifle so it should be fairly stable and it is firing about 1/2" groups at 35 yards. I listed this rifle as "used" on Gunbroker because of Hector's work. Since he completed the rifle, it has just sat in my vault and I have decided to sell it to fund other projects. Note that Héctor recommends lubing the pellets with T-9 liquid lubricant.
